    "Encouraged to freely explore and to make and monitor their own mistakes, Montessori-schooled children also exhibit a distinctive affective response to errors, processing their errors and successes comparatively neutral -whereas children who undergo traditional-schools' testing and grading in terms of success or failure, show strong aversive responses to mistakes (Denervaud et al., 2021).",
